article.headline: IUPUI 66, N. Dakota St. 52
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- Alex Young scored 23 points and IUPUI defeated North Dakota State, 66-52, in Summit League play on Thursday night. Young hit on 10 of 14 shots. Robert Glenn earned his third double-double of the season with 14 points and 12 rebounds. Leroy Nobles and John Ashworth both scored 10 points for the Jaguars (21-9, 14-3). The Bison (10-17, 7-10) were led by Michael Tveidt's 17 points and eight rebounds. Josh Vaughn added 12 points on 4 of 9 shooting from 3-point range. The Bison trailed 30-22 at the half but rallied to tie the score at 42-42 with 9:42 left to play. The Jaguars would go on a 12-4 run from there to take a 54-46 lead that would not be threatened the rest of the game. IUPUI has now locked up the second seed for the Summit League conference tournament.
